agents.outputHint:
A citation-attached concern register plus integrity lists and a validation summary.

1. Cited concern register — one entry per flagged concern, each containing:
   - a short id/label for the concern;
   - the concern statement exactly as received from s4 (tenant perspective, unaltered);
   - one or more exact clause references drawn verbatim from the s3 catalog (most granular available; list all contributing references);
   - a verbatim quote/excerpt of the operative lease language that grounds the concern;
   - an "omission" marker where the disadvantage stems from absent protection anchored to the cited governing clause.

2. Uncitable concerns — concerns that no catalogued clause can anchor, each with the reason.

3. Reconciliation needed — concerns whose asserted language is absent from or inconsistent with the catalog, each stating the specific mismatch.

4. Validation summary — total concerns received, total cited, total uncitable, total needing reconciliation (must sum to received), and an explicit statement that every concern in the cited register carries a specific catalogued clause reference and that no landlord-favorable/neutral framing was added.
